cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with pose estimation in color data. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The fact that it can handle occlusion and is agnostic to visual ambiguities suggests that it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of a visual loss function suggests that it could belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
